      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must hold ISO 9001 certification and maintain a formal regression test suite covering all turbulence model variants used in this COU.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is used; vendor holds ISO 9001 certification. Internal regression suite with 1,200 test cases executed at each release. All tests pass. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Convergence order must be demonstrated for the momentum and scalar transport equations via the method of manufactured solutions on geometries representative of the pump impeller channel.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to simplified 2-D impeller channel; observed order 1.87 for velocity and 1.72 for scalar transport. Full 3-D pump geometry MMS not completed. Achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3 — gap noted."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed on three systematically refined meshes; GCI on hemolysis index must be below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (4.2 M, 11.7 M, 28.4 M cells) generated with refinement ratio 1.41. GCI on hemolysis index: 3.8%. Richardson extrapolation applied. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented to within ±2% of target flow rates and rotational speeds; temperature and fluid viscosity must be measured and reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental dataset documents flow rates to ±3.1% and speed to ±1.8%. Fluid viscosity measured but temperature excursions during testing not fully characterized. Achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (E%, NRMSE) must be computed for all five operating points; uncertainty intervals must be propagated from experimental measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "E% computed for hemolysis index at all five operating points: mean 11.4%, max 18.2%. NRMSE = 0.12. Experimental uncertainty bands propagated via GUM framework. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be demonstrated to correlate with clinical hemolysis endpoints; the mapping from CFD shear stress to NIH must be explicitly documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH selected as primary QoI per ASTM F1841. Giersiepen power-law model maps shear stress exposure to hemolysis; model constants calibrated against in-vitro data. Clinical correlation documented. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry and at least three of five target operating points; blood analog fluid properties must match within 10%.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark uses identical generic pump geometry. Three of five VAD operating points are covered by benchmark data; two high-speed conditions are extrapolated. Blood analog (glycerin-water) viscosity within 8% of target. Achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residuals below 1e-5 for all equations; round-off error analysis must confirm double-precision arithmetic is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "All residuals converged below 1e-6 within 3,000 iterations. Double-precision arithmetic confirmed; round-off contribution to hemolysis index estimated at 0.02% via perturbation analysis. Required Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A documented simulation execution protocol and independent peer review of boundary condition setup must be completed before results are submitted.",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution protocol documented in internal SOP-CFD-012. Independent peer review conducted by two senior engineers not involved in the original setup. No setup errors identified. Required Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model must be justified through literature review and sensitivity analysis; alternative model forms must be evaluated.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on literature benchmark studies. Sensitivity analysis comparing SST k-omega, realizable k-epsilon, and RSM shows hemolysis index varies by up to 22% across model forms. Single model form adopted without full uncertainty quantification across alternatives. Achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, boundary conditions, hemolysis model constants) must have documented sources and uncertainty ranges; Monte Carlo propagation must be performed.",
      "rationale": "Fluid density, viscosity, and hemolysis model constants (C, alpha, beta) assigned probability distributions based on published calibration data. Monte Carlo with 500 samples performed; 95th-percentile hemolysis index reported. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples must be documented with lot numbers and preparation protocols; sample-to-sample variability must be reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark reports three independent experimental runs per operating point. Blood analog preparation documented with batch records. Inter-run variability for hemolysis index: CV = 6.3%. Required Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions and material properties applied in the CFD model must be demonstrated to match the experimental test conditions within stated tolerances for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this COU because the study is purely computational and does not involve a paired physical test article operated alongside the simulation. No physical prototype was fabricated for this assessment phase; therefore the factor was not evaluated. However, the FDA benchmark data used for validation was collected on a physical pump under conditions that may differ from the CFD boundary conditions in ways not fully characterized, and the factor status was recorded as 'not-assessed' rather than 'not-applicable', leaving the equivalency gap unquantified at Model Risk Level 3."
    }
